<task id="016" project="ai-spaarke-action-engine-r1">
  <metadata>
    <title>Azure AI Search — Provision spaarke-resource-registry-index on existing spaarke-search-dev</title>
    <phase>Phase 1: Foundation</phase>
    <status>not-started</status>
    <estimated-hours>4</estimated-hours>
    <dependencies>001, 011</dependencies>
    <blocks>022, 023, 024, 025, 026</blocks>
    <tags>azure, azure-search, ai, deploy</tags>
    <rigor-hint>FULL</rigor-hint>
    <rigor-reason>Provisions production-shaped infra on a shared Azure resource (`spaarke-search-dev`); schema is the semantic backing for `FindResources` meta-tool (NFR-01: p95 &lt; 200ms); a wrong schema forces a re-index across Tool Registry growth; tags include azure + deploy</rigor-reason>
    <parallel-group>B</parallel-group>
    <parallel-safe>true</parallel-safe>
    <parallel-reason>Provisions a NEW index `spaarke-resource-registry-index` on an existing Azure AI Search service. Does NOT modify BFF code, NOT modify `AddActionEngineModule.cs`, NOT modify `Program.cs`. Disjoint from tasks 014 (BFF DI + Program.cs) and 015 (PublicContracts facade). Resource creation only — no DI registration in this task. Depends on task 011 for the `sprk_toolregistry` shape, but does NOT modify it.</parallel-reason>
  </metadata>

  <prompt>
    Provision a NEW Azure AI Search index `spaarke-resource-registry-index` on the existing `spaarke-search-dev` service. Define the schema (vector + keyword fields for Tool Registry Discoverability per spec FR-08), semantic configuration, and vectorizer wiring against the existing OpenAI embedding deployment. Do NOT touch the existing `spaarke-file-index` infrastructure. Output: index live, schema documented, and a smoke-test query (zero documents — just structural query) succeeds with HTTP 200.
  </prompt>

  <role>
    SPAARKE Azure infra engineer experienced with Azure AI Search index provisioning via Bicep + REST API. You distinguish between the SERVICE (provisioned, existing — do not modify) and INDEXES on that service (new — what this task creates). You understand semantic search configuration, vectorizers, vector profiles, and the wire-up to an existing Azure OpenAI embedding deployment.
  </role>

  <goal>
    Three outcomes:

    1. **Index schema authored** at `infra/ai-search/spaarke-resource-registry-index/index-schema.json` — the Azure AI Search index definition. Fields per spec FR-08:
       - `resourceId` (Edm.String, key, retrievable, filterable)
       - `displayName` (Edm.String, retrievable, searchable)
       - `description` (Edm.String, retrievable, searchable)
       - `classification` (Edm.String, retrievable, filterable, facetable) — facet for filter-by-Deterministic/AI/Hybrid
       - `tenantId` (Edm.String, retrievable, filterable) — mandatory filter for tenant scoping (NFR-05)
       - `keywords` (Collection(Edm.String), retrievable, searchable, facetable)
       - `semanticDescription` (Edm.String, retrievable, searchable) — the primary semantic-search field per spec FR-08
       - `sampleInvocationsJson` (Edm.String, retrievable) — stringified JSON; not indexed for search
       - `costClass`, `latencyClass`, `authMode`, `modelTier` (Edm.String, retrievable, filterable, facetable) — Tool axes for filtered queries
       - `isAlwaysOnInAssistant` (Edm.Boolean, retrievable, filterable)
       - `evidenceRequired` (Edm.Boolean, retrievable, filterable)
       - `phaseRestrictions` (Collection(Edm.String), retrievable, filterable)
       - `promoteInContexts` (Collection(Edm.String), retrievable, filterable)
       - `descriptionVector` (Collection(Edm.Single), `dimensions = 1536` for `text-embedding-ada-002` or `dimensions = 3072` for `text-embedding-3-large` — pick to match the existing OpenAI deployment on `spaarke-openai-dev`)
       - Vector profile + HNSW algorithm config
       - Semantic config: title field = `displayName`; content fields = `description`, `semanticDescription`, `keywords`

    2. **Bicep module** at `infra/ai-search/spaarke-resource-registry-index/main.bicep` — declarative IaC for the index. Parameter for the existing service name (`spaarke-search-dev`); module deploys ONLY the new index, NOT the service. Uses `Microsoft.Search/searchServices/indexes@2023-11-01` (or current GA API version).

    3. **Index deployed to dev** — the Bicep module run against the resource group containing `spaarke-search-dev`. Verified by REST API GET on the new index URL returning HTTP 200 and the schema matching.

    Deliverable: index exists; schema documented at `infra/ai-search/spaarke-resource-registry-index/README.md`; structural smoke-test query (e.g., `POST /indexes/spaarke-resource-registry-index/docs/search?api-version=2023-11-01` with `search=*`) returns HTTP 200 with 0 documents.
  </goal>

  <context>
    <background>
      **Existing service**: `spaarke-search-dev` is the existing Azure AI Search service in the dev resource group. It already hosts `spaarke-file-index` (document RAG). This task adds a NEW index ALONGSIDE — does NOT modify the existing index, does NOT modify the service tier or replication.

      **Schema source**: spec.md FR-08 + design §5 + the `sprk_toolregistry` Dataverse shape from task 011. The semantic search field is `discoverabilityJson.semanticDescription`, which is flattened into a top-level `semanticDescription` field on the search index (Azure AI Search doesn't search nested JSON directly).

      **Vectorizer**: the index uses `text-embedding-ada-002` or `text-embedding-3-large` (whichever is deployed on `spaarke-openai-dev`). Check the existing deployment before authoring the vector profile — the `dimensions` count MUST match (1536 for ada-002, 3072 for embedding-3-large).

      **Indexer**: NOT in scope for this task. This task creates the INDEX (the storage shape). Phase 2 (task 022 or 025) will create the indexer or push-API loader that hydrates the index from `sprk_toolregistry` records.

      **No BFF code change**: this task creates Azure infra only. The BFF client wiring (search client registration in `AddActionEngineModule.cs`) is a Phase 2 task. This task does NOT modify any BFF files — that's why it's parallel-safe with 014 and 015.

      **NFR-01 latency target**: `FindResources` p95 &lt; 200ms. The index design must support that — HNSW vector profile + semantic ranker + tenant filter. Document the expected p95 in the README; validation is a Phase 6 load test.

      **NFR-05 tenant isolation**: every query against this index MUST filter by `tenantId`. The index doesn't enforce this directly — the BFF query layer does (task 022). Document the requirement in the README.
    </background>
    <relevant-files>
      <file>infra/ai-search/ (existing; check for parallel index modules to mirror)</file>
      <file>projects/ai-spaarke-action-engine-r1/spec.md</file>
      <file>projects/ai-spaarke-action-engine-r1/design.md</file>
      <file>docs/architecture/auth-azure-resources.md</file>
    </relevant-files>
  </context>

  <constraints>
    <constraint source="ADR-001">Placement: Action Engine in BFF, NOT in a separate Function App. The search index is infra (lives in Azure resource group), not code — placement constraint applies to consumers (BFF query layer), not to the index itself.</constraint>
    <constraint source="ADR-029">BFF publish-size delta ≤ 5 MB compressed. This task does NOT add packages to the BFF csproj, so the publish-size impact is zero. Verified.</constraint>
    <constraint source="bff-extensions.md">Pre-merge checklist: placement decision (index is infra; consumer is BFF per ADR-013), ADRs cited, publish-size verified (no impact), no new HIGH-sev CVE (no BFF package changes), feature-module DI (consumer registration is Phase 2, not this task).</constraint>
    <constraint source="project">Provision the index on the EXISTING service `spaarke-search-dev`. Do NOT create a new service. Do NOT modify the service tier, replication, or partitioning.</constraint>
    <constraint source="project">Do NOT touch the existing `spaarke-file-index`. Verify by Bicep scope and by REST GET on that index before + after.</constraint>
    <constraint source="project">Tenant isolation: every query against this index MUST filter by `tenantId`. The index schema includes the field; query enforcement is a Phase 2 concern documented in the README.</constraint>
    <constraint source="project">Vector dimensions match the existing OpenAI embedding deployment on `spaarke-openai-dev`. Mis-matched dimensions cause indexing failures.</constraint>
  </constraints>

