    <patterns>
      <pattern name="azure-deploy (Bicep + script)" location=".claude/skills/azure-deploy/SKILL.md">Bicep authoring + deployment pattern; use for the new index module.</pattern>
      <pattern name="Existing AI Search index modules" location="infra/ai-search/">Mirror the existing module structure (likely `spaarke-file-index` is the closest sibling); copy patterns for vectorizer config, semantic config, and IaC parameters.</pattern>
    </patterns>
  </knowledge>

  <steps>
    <step order="0">Context check: confirm working tree clean, branch is `work/ai-spaarke-action-engine-r1`, baseline build passes, tasks 001 + 011 status are ✅. Load the `azure-deploy` skill. (task-execute Step 0)</step>
    <step order="1">Inspect existing Azure AI Search infra:
      - `az search service show --name spaarke-search-dev --resource-group &lt;rg-name&gt;` — confirm tier, replicas, partitions
      - `az search service list-admin-keys` — capture admin key for REST GETs (do NOT commit)
      - REST GET on existing `spaarke-file-index` to capture its schema shape — mirror conventions where appropriate (analyzers, language, etc.)
    </step>
    <step order="2">Inspect existing Azure OpenAI deployment on `spaarke-openai-dev` to determine the embedding model + dimensions:
      - `az cognitiveservices account deployment list --name spaarke-openai-dev --resource-group &lt;rg-name&gt;` — find the embedding deployment
      - Note: dimensions = 1536 for `text-embedding-ada-002`; dimensions = 3072 for `text-embedding-3-large`
      - Record the choice in `notes/decisions/task-016-embedding-model.md`.
    </step>
    <step order="3">Read spec.md FR-08, design §5 (Tool Registry section), and task 011's schema doc (`docs/data-model/action-engine-entities.md` `sprk_toolregistry` section) to align field names between Dataverse + Azure AI Search.</step>
    <step order="4">Author `infra/ai-search/spaarke-resource-registry-index/index-schema.json` — full Azure AI Search index definition per the `&lt;goal&gt;` field list. Include:
      - Vector profile referencing `spaarke-openai-dev` via Azure AI Search vectorizer config (using managed identity if the service supports it; otherwise API key from Key Vault per project secrets policy)
      - Semantic config with title = `displayName`, content fields = `description` + `semanticDescription` + `keywords`
      - HNSW algorithm config with default parameters
      - Suggester on `displayName` + `keywords` for typeahead (optional but useful)
    </step>
    <step order="5">Author `infra/ai-search/spaarke-resource-registry-index/main.bicep` — Bicep module that deploys the index. Uses `Microsoft.Search/searchServices/indexes@2023-11-01` resource. Parameter `searchServiceName` (default `spaarke-search-dev`). Reads the JSON schema from `index-schema.json` via `loadJsonContent()` Bicep function.</step>
    <step order="6">Validate Bicep locally: `az bicep build --file infra/ai-search/spaarke-resource-registry-index/main.bicep` — MUST succeed.</step>
    <step order="7">Deploy to dev: `az deployment group create --resource-group &lt;rg-name&gt; --template-file infra/ai-search/spaarke-resource-registry-index/main.bicep` (use `--what-if` first to confirm changes are additive only — should show ONE create: the new index).</step>
    <step order="8">Smoke-test the deployed index:
      - REST GET on the new index URL: `GET https://spaarke-search-dev.search.windows.net/indexes/spaarke-resource-registry-index?api-version=2023-11-01` MUST return HTTP 200 with the schema we authored
      - Structural search query: `POST /indexes/spaarke-resource-registry-index/docs/search?api-version=2023-11-01` with body `{"search": "*"}` MUST return HTTP 200 with 0 documents (no docs indexed yet — by design)
      - Verify no regression on `spaarke-file-index`: REST GET MUST return its existing schema unchanged
    </step>
    <step order="9">Author `infra/ai-search/spaarke-resource-registry-index/README.md` — index overview:
      - Purpose: Tool Registry semantic discovery (spec FR-08 + NFR-01)
      - Field-by-field schema with `Dataverse → Index` mapping (so task 022's indexer/loader knows the projection)
      - Tenant isolation requirement (NFR-05): every query MUST filter by `tenantId`
      - Latency target: `FindResources` p95 &lt; 200ms (NFR-01); load test in Phase 6 validates
      - Embedding model + dimensions (from step 2)
    </step>
    <step order="10">Run quality gates per task-execute Step 9.5: `code-review` on the Bicep + JSON schema + README; `adr-check` confirms ADR-029 (no BFF impact), bff-extensions.md (placement: index is infra; BFF consumer is Phase 2). The `bff-extensions.md` pre-merge checklist applies but most items are N/A here (no BFF code change).</step>
    <step order="11">Verify BFF baseline build still passes: `dotnet build src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/` exits 0. (Should be unaffected — no BFF code change.)</step>
    <step order="12">Update `tasks/TASK-INDEX.md`: mark task 016 ✅; verify it unblocks tasks 022, 023, 024, 025, 026. Reset `current-task.md` to point to next pending task in Group B (or signal Phase 1 complete if 010-016 all ✅).</step>
    <step order="13">Document any deviations from this plan in `projects/ai-spaarke-action-engine-r1/notes/handoffs/task-016-handoff.md` and add a brief commit message recap. Commit message MUST note the existing service used, the embedding model + dimensions, and confirm no regression on `spaarke-file-index`.</step>
  </steps>

