  <acceptance-criteria>
    <criterion testable="true">Bicep module exists at `infra/ai-search/spaarke-resource-registry-index/main.bicep` and compiles cleanly: `az bicep build` exits 0.</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">Index schema at `infra/ai-search/spaarke-resource-registry-index/index-schema.json` includes all required fields per spec FR-08 + vector profile + semantic config; validated by JSON schema lint + structural inspection.</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">Index deployed to dev: REST GET on `https://spaarke-search-dev.search.windows.net/indexes/spaarke-resource-registry-index?api-version=2023-11-01` returns HTTP 200 with the deployed schema.</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">Structural smoke-test query (`search=*`) returns HTTP 200 with 0 documents.</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">Existing `spaarke-file-index` schema unchanged; verified by REST GET before + after.</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">Vector dimensions in the index schema match the existing OpenAI embedding deployment on `spaarke-openai-dev`; choice documented in `notes/decisions/task-016-embedding-model.md`.</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">README documents the full Dataverse → Index field mapping for the Phase 2 indexer/loader task.</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">BFF baseline build still passes: `dotnet build src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/` exits 0 (no BFF code change in this task — verifies parallel-safe with tasks 014 + 015).</criterion>
  </acceptance-criteria>

  <notes>
    This task is INFRA-ONLY. No BFF code change. That's why it's parallel-safe with tasks 014 (BFF DI module) and 015 (PublicContracts facade) — none of these tasks touch the same files.

    Do NOT add Azure AI Search client packages to `Sprk.Bff.Api.csproj` in this task. That's a Phase 2 concern (task 022 or 025 — whichever owns `FindResources` impl). Adding it here risks publish-size budget pressure without the corresponding consumer code.

    Vector dimensions are LOCKED at index creation. If you pick 1536 (ada-002) and later want to switch to 3072 (embedding-3-large), you MUST recreate the index. Verify the existing deployment on `spaarke-openai-dev` BEFORE authoring the schema.

    Tenant isolation: the index has the `tenantId` field, but enforcement is at QUERY time — every BFF query MUST filter by tenantId. Document this in the README so task 022 doesn't forget. Index-level isolation (separate index per tenant) is OUT of scope for MVP — design lean is single multi-tenant index with mandatory tenant filter.

    The semantic config makes `FindResources` work. Without it, the index is only a vector + keyword surface (still useful but the semantic ranker noticeably improves p95 quality). Verify the existing service tier supports semantic search (Basic SKU does NOT; Standard or above does). If the existing service is Basic, escalate — semantic search is a hard NFR-01 dependency.

    `spaarke-file-index` smoke test (REST GET before + after) is mandatory. The biggest risk of this task is accidentally modifying the wrong index. Bicep scoping should prevent it, but verify empirically.

    `bff-extensions.md` checklist: most items are N/A here (no BFF code change). Cite the assessment in the PR description to show you considered it — placement decision (index is infra), ADRs cited (ADR-029 N/A, no publish-size impact), no new HIGH-sev CVE (no BFF package changes), feature-module DI (consumer in Phase 2). Recording the N/A items is itself the discipline.
  </notes>

